						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying near the house of Tīrthagauḍa. </p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is a damaged inscription. It records a gift of land made for digging a well on the boundary of Amalagoḷḷa by Siriyapagauḍa and others of Suḷa. The record is written by Saṅkara. In characters of about 17th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
